            <commentid>33679</commentid>
            <who name="Daniel Wagner">daniel.wagner</who>
            <bug_when>2013-08-21 15:58:11 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>This seems to be a problem with the comments parser. The event in question is documented like this:

/** Fired before the context menu is opened. */

ecmascript.frontend.Comment.parseNode returns a result with an empty string as the value for &quot;text&quot;

If the comment looks like this:

/**
  * Fired before the context menu is opened.
  */

&quot;text&quot; has the expected value.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
